# Firebase Services

## Storage split

- **RTDB** — live battle state only (`battles/{id}/...`)
- **Firestore** — rooms, teams, championships, checklist
- Do not store live turn sync in Firestore

## Client init

- Lazy: `firebase/client.ts` → `getDb()` for lobby, checklist
- Eager: `firebase.ts` when RTDB/auth needed immediately

## Security

- Never log API keys, service account JSON, or user tokens
- Server-only: `FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_KEY`
- Rules files: `database.rules.json`, `firestore.rules`

## RTDB paths

```
battles/{id}/meta | public | private/{uid}
battles/{id}/turns/{n}/choices/{uid}
battles/{id}/turns/{n}/resolution  ← server writes only
```

## Testing

- RTDB changes: `npm run test:unit` + `npm run test:security`
